result.name: Ho Lee Fook

reviews.text: The service was very good, the staff knows the menu well and can easily guide you to find the right choice for your diet. Flavors of the food overall was good, seasoning on the other hand can be intense, so be careful if you are sensitive. I ordered a bamboo salad and it was crunchy and delicious - slightly more dressing than I prefer, I might mention that next time when ordering. For the main course I choose a tofu and omnipork (vegetarian) dish; flavor was great - perfect amount of garlic but slightly too salty even when mixed with the steamed rice. They ended up taking it off the bill, so that was very nice of them. For dessert - Breakfast 2.0 - simply said - heavenly. Crunchy, sweet, refreshing and there was a special taste that made it a unique experience. I would definitely eat again at this place, but would want a thank you and good bye next time... However, this restaurant is absolutely worth the hype and money. Go for it!

Cool fusion Chinese restaurant operated by Aussies bringing a touch of western flair to traditional Asian dishes.

The dark underground ambient of the restaurant is chic, dishes are surprisingly fresh and tasty, service is great giving an awesome experience all round.

If you find the Chinese restaurants in Hong Kong intimidating because of the language barriers or service lacking, I recommend you try Ho Lee Fook next time, this is definitely not a tourist trap!

A fabulous night of food.

We ordered a mix of starters and mains, everything was just fantastic.

The prawn toast was sublime, and the chicken wings moorish.

The staff were all energetic and helpful. 

I can't say more good things, just go!

This place is incredible... It was my wife's birthday and this is worth the trip to Hong Kong. Simply the best meat I have ever eaten...Crunch on the outside and tender and pure pleasure on the inside. Amazing. They also included the meat shavings which is spectacular as well. The dimsum also good.

Yum. Long wait to get in but worth the wait. My only reason for not 5 stars is that the plates are very small but so delicious that you have to buy two of them... Make the plates a bit bigger and it's 5/5
